PN,30201
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779843788
OL,3,CTemperatures to cool for some after
OL,4,Csix water deaths in record-breaking UK
OL,5,Cheat
OL,7,FTemperatures are expected to cool
OL,8,Fslightly in parts of the UK after
OL,9,Fseveral days of record-breaking heat
OL,10,Fand the deaths of six people who got
OL,11,Finto trouble in open water.
OL,13,FThe Met Office said Tuesday was the
OL,14,Fhottest day in May on record for both
OL,15,FEngland and Wales, with Kew Gardens
OL,16,Fprovisionally reaching 35.1C and
OL,17,FCardiff Bute Park reaching 32.9C.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779843788
OL,3,CTemperatures to cool for some after
OL,4,Csix water deaths in record-breaking UK
OL,5,Cheat
OL,7,FThe weather service said cloud and a
OL,8,Fdeveloping easterly flow of wind on
OL,9,FWednesday would lead to a "reduction
OL,10,Fin temperature highs for many areas" `
OL,11,Falthough south-west England may still
OL,12,Fsee 32C-33C.
OL,14,FHighs of 32C are forecast for Thursday
OL,15,Fin London and the East Midlands, with
OL,16,Ftemperatures on Friday potentially
OL,17,Freaching 30C in London and East Anglia.
OL,26,@qD@[OUrD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779843788
OL,3,CTemperatures to cool for some after
OL,4,Csix water deaths in record-breaking UK
OL,5,Cheat
OL,7,FBy Sunday, the warmest air is expected
OL,8,Fto have cleared away to the south with
OL,9,Ftemperatures closer to, but mostly
OL,10,Fabove, average for the time of year
OL,11,Ffor the whole of the UK.
OL,13,FPeople have died after struggling in
OL,14,Fopen water in South Yorkshire, West
OL,15,FYorkshire, Devon and Cornwall,
OL,16,FWarwickshire, Lincolnshire and
OL,17,FLancashire in recent days.
OL,19,FDeclan Sawyer, 15, died after getting
OL,20,Finto trouble at Swanholme Lakes,
OL,21,FLincoln, on Sunday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779843788
OL,3,CTemperatures to cool for some after
OL,4,Csix water deaths in record-breaking UK
OL,5,Cheat
OL,7,FA 13-year-old boy died after getting
OL,8,Finto difficulty at Leadbeater Dam,
OL,9,Fnear Halifax, West Yorkshire, on
OL,10,FMonday and the body of a teenage girl
OL,11,Fwas recovered from the water at
OL,12,FKingsbury Water Park, Warwickshire.
OL,14,FA spokesperson for West Yorkshire
OL,15,FPolice said the teenage boy was pulled
OL,16,Ffrom the water and taken to hospital,
OL,17,Fwhere he was pronounced dead.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779843788
OL,3,CTemperatures to cool for some after
OL,4,Csix water deaths in record-breaking UK
OL,5,Cheat
OL,7,FThe same day, a man in his 60s died of
OL,8,Fcardiac arrest after entering the sea
OL,9,Fat Tregirls Beach, Padstow, to help
OL,10,Ftwo family members who were in
OL,11,Fdifficulty, Devon and Cornwall Police
OL,12,Fsaid.
OL,14,FThe body of a fourth teenager was
OL,15,Frecovered from the water at Rother
OL,16,FValley Country Park, Rotherham, in the
OL,17,Fearly hours of Tuesday morning, South
OL,18,FYorkshire Police said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779843788
OL,3,CTemperatures to cool for some after
OL,4,Csix water deaths in record-breaking UK
OL,5,Cheat
OL,7,FAnd on Tuesday evening, Lancashire
OL,8,FPolice said a body had been recovered
OL,9,Ffrom the River Ribble after a 12-year-
OL,10,Fold boy got into difficulty while
OL,11,Fswimming with friends at Ribchester.
OL,13,FThe RNLI warned of the "very real
OL,14,Frisk" of swimming in open water during
OL,15,Fthe heatwave.
OL,17,FThe charity said that while
OL,18,Ftemperatures have hit record highs for
OL,19,FMay, water temperatures remained low
OL,20,Fand this could lead to cold water
OL,21,Fshock.
OL,26,@uD@XOUvD@EO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779843788
OL,3,CTemperatures to cool for some after
OL,4,Csix water deaths in record-breaking UK
OL,5,Cheat
OL,7,FThe National Fire Chiefs Council has
OL,8,Falso issued a water safety warning and
OL,9,Furged families to speak to children
OL,10,Fabout the risks of unsupervised
OL,11,Fswimming in rivers, lakes, quarries,
OL,12,Fcanals and reservoirs.
OL,14,FTrain services across Britain were
OL,15,Fdisrupted as temperatures soared, with
OL,16,FNetwork Rail imposing a series of
OL,17,Fspeed restrictions on tracks to keep
OL,18,Ftrains safe on Tuesday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779843788
OL,3,CTemperatures to cool for some after
OL,4,Csix water deaths in record-breaking UK
OL,5,Cheat
OL,7,FThe UK experienced a "tropical night"
OL,8,Fon Monday as the record for the
OL,9,Fwarmest minimum temperature for May
OL,10,Fwas broken for the second consecutive
OL,11,Fday.
OL,13,FTemperatures did not fall below 20C
OL,14,Fovernight on Monday in parts of the
OL,15,FUK, with 21.3C recorded at Kenley
OL,16,FAirfield, south London.
OL,18,FMet Office meteorologist Alex Burkill
OL,19,Fsaid the "exceedingly hot"
OL,20,Ftemperatures were "exceptional".
OL,26,@oD@VOUoD@eO]{D@JOU{D@ZO]|D@SOU|D@_O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779843788
OL,3,CTemperatures to cool for some after
OL,4,Csix water deaths in record-breaking UK
OL,5,Cheat
OL,7,FMr Burkill added: "It really is an
OL,8,Fexceptionally warm or very hot spell
OL,9,Fat the moment.
OL,11,F"For any time of the year it's hot,
OL,12,Fbut for May in particular ` it is
OL,13,Fstill meteorological spring.
OL,15,F"In terms of how ground-breaking, how
OL,16,Fhistoric it is ` it's very similar to
OL,17,Fthat first time that we reached 40C.
OL,19,F"The fact that we've exceeded the May
OL,20,Ftemperature by such an amount really
OL,21,Fis extraordinary and quite worrying."
OL,26,@oD@SOUsD@AOUwD@AOU{D@AOU}D@eO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30210
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779843788
OL,3,CTemperatures to cool for some after
OL,4,Csix water deaths in record-breaking UK
OL,5,Cheat
OL,7,FThe UK Health Security Agency (UKHSA)
OL,8,Fsaid amber heat-health alerts for the
OL,9,FSouth West, South East, London, East
OL,10,Fand West Midlands and the East of
OL,11,FEngland will remain in place until 5pm
OL,12,Fon Thursday, with yellow heat-health
OL,13,Falerts for the North West and North
OL,14,FEast.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30211
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1779843788
OL,3,CTemperatures to cool for some after
OL,4,Csix water deaths in record-breaking UK
OL,5,Cheat
OL,7,FThe Met Office said a climate
OL,8,Fattribution study published last
OL,9,Fsummer by its scientists found that
OL,10,Fthe chances of surpassing the May
OL,11,Ftemperature record "have been
OL,12,Fincreasing as our climate changes as a
OL,13,Fconsequence of human greenhouse gas
OL,14,Femissions".
OL,16,FThe study found that breaking the
OL,17,Fprevious 32.8C May record was "around
OL,18,Fthree times more likely now in our
OL,19,Fcurrent climate than it would have
OL,20,Fbeen in a natural climate not impacted
OL,21,Fby greenhouse gas emissions".
OL,26,@sD@TOUvD@JO]yD@_OU}D@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/11
